TITLE: Defining templ Page Structure
DESCRIPTION: Creates a templ page that includes placeholders for React components and loads a JavaScript bundle. This structure allows for server-side rendering with client-side React integration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/a-h/templ/blob/main/docs/docs/03-syntax-and-usage/17-using-react-with-templ.md#2025-04-18_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: templ
CODE:
```
package main

templ page() {
	<html>
		<body>
			<div id="react-header"></div>
			<div id="react-content"></div>
			<div>This is server-side content from templ.</div>
			<!-- Load the React bundle created using esbuild -->
			<script src="static/index.js"></script>
		</body>
	</html>
}
```

