TITLE: Creating UI Components with Templ Templates
DESCRIPTION: Templ components that render the counter application UI, including the count display and submission form. These components create the HTML structure with two buttons for incrementing global and user-specific counters.
SOURCE: https://github.com/a-h/templ/blob/main/docs/docs/05-server-side-rendering/02-example-counter-application.md#2025-04-18_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: templ
CODE:
```
package main

import "strconv"

templ counts(global, user int) {
	<div>Global: { strconv.Itoa(global) }</div>
	<div>User: { strconv.Itoa(user) }</div>
}

templ form() {
	<form action="/" method="POST">
		<div><button type="submit" name="global" value="global">Global</button></div>
		<div><button type="submit" name="user" value="user">User</button></div>
	</form>
}

templ page(global, user int) {
	@counts(global, user)
	@form()
}
```

