TITLE: Disabling Cache for Static Assets in Development
DESCRIPTION: Go middleware function to disable caching of static assets in development mode by setting the Cache-Control header to no-store, preventing browsers from using stale cached versions after changes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/a-h/templ/blob/main/docs/docs/09-developer-tools/04-live-reload-with-other-tools.md#2025-04-18_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
var dev = true

func disableCacheInDevMode(next http.Handler) http.Handler {
	if !dev {
		return next
	}
	return http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {
		w.Header().Set("Cache-Control", "no-store")
		next.ServeHTTP(w, r)
	})
}

mux.Handle("/assets/", 
  disableCacheInDevMode(
    http.StripPrefix("/assets", 
      http.FileServer(http.Dir("assets")))))
```

